# Salesforce metadata under force-app/ is NOT prettier-formatted:
#   - Retrieved standard metadata is reference state and drifts each platform
#     release; reformatting it churns thousands of files and risks deploy-time
#     diffs. The CLI's native (`sf project retrieve`) format is the contract.
#   - The vendored open-source accelerators keep their upstream formatting.
#   Our own Apex/LWC is kept clean by convention; eslint (`npm run lint`) covers
#   it. Prettier governs the project's docs, scripts, and config.
force-app/
